      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "### 3) MECHANISTIC BASIS (interaction with CYP2D6)\n- Likely binding mode:\n  - **Protonated tertiary amine** engages **Asp301** (salt bridge / ionic H-bond).\n  - **Phenyl rings** occupy hydrophobic pockets, stabilizing the complex.\n  - The sulfonamide phenyl and anisole ring can contribute to **high residence time** via hydrophobic contacts.\n- This binding can **block access of substrates** to the heme catalytic center, producing **reversible inhibition** (typical for many basic, lipophilic CYP2D6 inhibitors).",
