      "content": "### 5) VERIFICATION / UNCERTAINTY CHECK\n- **Potential counterpoint:** The molecule has **no H-bond donors**, and the sulfonamide reduces basicity at that N (but the key basic center is the tertiary amine, so this is not disqualifying).\n- **Steric/bulk effects:** The bicyclic framework is bulky; in some cases excessive steric hindrance can reduce fit to CYP2D6. However, many potent 2D6 inhibitors are also bulky as long as the **cationic anchor** can align with Asp301 and hydrophobes can pack.\n- **Net:** No internal contradiction\u2014the dominant features still favor inhibition. Confidence not \u201chigh\u201d because actual inhibition potency depends on precise 3D alignment and lipophilicity/ionization balance.",
